        "created_at": "2025-11-02T20:34:42.858Z",
        "cooked": "<p><strong>2013 Zind Humbrecht Muscat</strong> - if this were Muskrat Love it would be closer to the version that America did than the one that Captain and Tennille did.   It is 12% alcohol and is a slightly soft wine with slightly low acidity, but the usual enticing tropical fruit aromas and only a slight terminal sweetness, showing otherwise as quite dry.  Pleasant wine that won\u2019t get in the way of the conversation.  More a summer sipper but I came across it while trying to find something else and thought I\u2019d try it.  Many people look on this grape as producing either a summer sipper or a sweet dessert wine.  This was much closer to the former.</p>",
